<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The stock market crash of 1929 affected the broader economy by:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Only impacting wealthy investors</option>
            <option letter="b">Triggering bank failures and business closures</option>
            <option letter="c">Improving international trade</option>
            <option letter="d">Increasing consumer spending</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The 1929 stock market crash triggered a chain reaction throughout the economy. The collapse in stock values led to bank failures as loans went unpaid, businesses closing due to lack of capital and declining consumer spending, and a general loss of confidence in the economic system. These cascading effects helped transform the crash into the Great Depression, affecting all sectors of society.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
